properties.areaDesc: Koochiching; North St. Louis; North Itasca
properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 12 at 4:27AM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS THIS MORNING THROUGH THURSDAY WITH
ACCUMULATING SNOW AND BLOWING SNOW ALONG THE SOUTH SHORE...

.Snow and lake effect snow will impact the South Shore Wednesday
through Thursday morning. The greatest snowfall accumulations of
4 to 8 inches are forecast for the northern portions of Ashland
and Iron counties, with lesser amounts of 2 to 5 inches
elsewhere. Blowing snow and dangerous wind chills to 35 below are
also expected.

Bitterly cold wind chills are expected across northeastern
Minnesota and northwestern Wisconsin late this morning through
Thursday. Wind chill values as low as -30 will be possible across
northeastern Minnesota late this morning through the afternoon.
Tonight into Thursday morning, widespread wind chill values
ranging from -20 to -40 are likely away from Lake Superior with
some values approaching -50 near the International Border.

* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as 30
below zero late this morning into this afternoon, and as low as 45
below zero late tonight into Thursday morning.

* WHERE...Koochiching, North St. Louis and North Itasca
Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Bois Forte
Band, Deer Creek and, Nett Lake areas.

* WHEN...From 9 AM this morning to noon CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM THIS MORNING TO NOON CST THURSDAY
